The paper deals with the problem of detecting dependencies among variables in a quantified boolean formula, which is a topic in logic and automated reasoning. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The use of resolution paths and the focus on minimizing false positives suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the topic of dependencies among variables could also be relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
